<!-- CANTIDAD DE TRANSACCIONES -->
<%# The problem is a mismatch between chart libraries:
1. What's installed: ApexCharts gem and loaded via CDN (line 25 in _header.html.erb)
2. What's being used: Chartkick helpers (column_chart, pie_chart) in the partials
3. What's missing: Chartkick gem and its dependencies (Chart.js)
In importmap.rb:37-38, Chartkick is commented out:
# pin "chartkick", to: "chartkick.js"
# pin "Chart.bundle", to: "Chart.bundle.js"
In Gemfile:59, only ApexCharts is installed:
gem 'apexcharts'
Why it fails sometimes
When transactions_and_points loads first, it tries to use Chartkick helpers that reference non-existent JavaScript, causing the Turbo frame for customer_graphs to fail when it loads later. The execution order and Turbo's caching create inconsistent behavior.
Recommended Solution
Replace Chartkick with ApexCharts since ApexCharts is already installed and loaded. This involves:
1. Remove Chartkick calls from partials
2. Create ApexCharts equivalents using existing helper methods
3. Add Stimulus controllers for chart initialization
Alternative: Install Chartkick properly if you prefer keeping the current code structure.%>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xl-6">
      <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h4 class="header-title">CANTIDAD DE TRANSACCIONES</h4>
          <% series = [{name: "Transacciones", data: get_transaction_count(@movements) } ] %>
          <% options = {
            xtitle: 'Meses',
            ytitle: 'Cantidad de Transacciones',
            stacked: true
          } %>
          <%= column_chart(series, {**options, theme: 'palette4'}) %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

<!-- PUNTOS OTORGADOS Y CANJEADOS -->
    <div class="col-xl-6">
      <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h4 class="header-title">PUNTOS OTORGADOS Y CANJEADOS</h4>
          <% series = [{
            name: "Puntos", 
            data: {
              "Puntos Otorgados"=> get_four_mounth_awarded_points(@movements),
              "Puntos Canjeados"=> get_four_mounth_excheange_points(@movements)
            }
          }]%>
          <% options = {
            xtitle: 'Tipo de puntos',
            ytitle: 'Cantidad de Puntos',
            stacked: true
          } %>
          <%= column_chart(series, {**options, theme: 'palette4'}) %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>